<body>
    <h1>20260609 LapuLapu ETS, GOCC and Obs</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"946e9de56191"><strong><u>Key Agenda Items</u></stron=
g></p>
<ul local-id=3D"90c4c73a-79ed-4023-9781-9db8d6bc388f">
<li local-id=3D"e83277fb-0f09-4b7c-a94d-5faa30deef34">
<p local-id=3D"795c9002417b"><strong>File Share</strong>: ServerF <strong>F=
ile Transfer</strong>: MFT, WSFTP <strong>Batch jobs</strong>: CAWLA</p>
<ul local-id=3D"23d65d5b967f">
<li local-id=3D"41368dc292de">
<p local-id=3D"d5a5760b72cf">Add Joan and Rowena to weekly meeting to repre=
sent GBO</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"1cd8f0215728" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>ACL mon=
itoring proposal:</strong> Assess whether GOCC can monitor shared-folder AC=
L compliance against the standard <code>mfcgd\acl_{folder_name}_{tier}</cod=
e> model, including detection of missing required groups (<code>_C</code>, =
<code>_R</code>), incorrect rights, unexpected additional principals, and A=
CL read failures. Key design consideration: unmanaged folders will also gen=
erate findings, so scope control and false-positive handling would need to =
be defined.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5c997315f7d0" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">Apply the same =
<strong>permission and retention profiles</strong> from <strong>SharePoint<=
/strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"7d49f9e115b5" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong> </stro=
ng>- <a data-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://manulife-ets.atlass=
ian.net/wiki/x/AQAk-AI" local-id=3D"289ba9bc1219" rel=3D"nofollow">https://=
manulife-ets.atlassian.net/wiki/x/AQAk-AI</a></p>
<p local-id=3D"034356056d80"></p>
<ul local-id=3D"a22c7dd5843d">
<li local-id=3D"6c2cd1aa357a">
<p local-id=3D"a6188aa429ca"><strong>Dashboards </strong>- Currently in Bet=
a-test with AQA users, tighten alerting parameters and reporting</p>
<ul local-id=3D"21a33249-6da4-4d32-8712-fbdd8bc5cd2d">
<li local-id=3D"c57598ed-ff33-4f5e-9ffa-43effa574b53">
<p local-id=3D"50b0320958d5">Developer Experience Dashboard</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"48f429cee395" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"id-20260=
609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-=F0=9F=94=B4Alerts(push,real-time)">=F0=9F=94=B4 =
Alerts (push, real-time)</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"2d1d3c7df041">
<li local-id=3D"298fb0d4035c">
<p local-id=3D"daefaad54a4d">Only actionable signals</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4f1ad8aa8011">
<p local-id=3D"dc1003c480f7">Routed to responders</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"7202e8398d71" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"id-20260=
609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-=F0=9F=9F=A1Dashboard(pull)">=F0=9F=9F=A1 Dashboa=
rd (pull)</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"9b0af5eb56bb">
<li local-id=3D"01dbfc6a34d8">
<p local-id=3D"b047ba1d1708">All data, all environments</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"487c78c7c2d6" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"id-20260=
609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-=F0=9F=9F=A2Morningemail(summary)">=F0=9F=9F=A2 M=
orning email (summary)</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"4b32d75c4bb5">
<li local-id=3D"054cc72f6419">
<p local-id=3D"0e570994e3bf">One concise view of system health</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5328c8f2-57fb-4507-a405-b8ad0381f91e">
<p local-id=3D"846ca4adfb46"><strong>MMM L2 Coverage</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"72d254fb-7ea4-43e1-b9af-a2cd947d9243">
<li local-id=3D"a02e6623-b551-4960-a428-31f358456b28">
<p local-id=3D"a92798ce65a5">Check with Harish for updates</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"78b2c683eb74">
<p local-id=3D"987813fbf0b0">APM rollout to non-AKS starting with <strong>I=
ngenium</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"d3f2d9b0-a23a-4205-b646-88f3f8f2cdcf">
<li local-id=3D"086fe7af-205f-466b-9091-f5581621ebe9">
<p local-id=3D"d049988d5c03"><strong>Jesus </strong>and <strong>Prabu </str=
ong>and <strong>Angelito Darjuan </strong>working on Prod (CHG#)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b10c17e0-f3d2-4c9a-a9e3-37f59f877472">
<p local-id=3D"eb96e0bad46e">Lower environment implementation is complete</=
p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"52479a20ea30">
<p local-id=3D"59cf1713f521"><a href=3D"https://manulife-ets.atlassian.net/=
wiki/spaces/GOCC/pages/16487481504/ADX" data-linked-resource-id=3D"16487481=
504" data-linked-resource-version=3D"2" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">=
ADX</a> - Establish coverage in Asia thru GOCC</p>
<ul local-id=3D"25b4578919eb">
<li local-id=3D"c0a71aaff1e0">
<p local-id=3D"114635c73dc5">Jonan will review capability and feasibility o=
f establishing some coverage for Asia</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"427f0e91-c626-41f7-a417-5c87496f1fb7">
<p local-id=3D"62a8cc8c8eb7"><a href=3D"https://manulife-ets.atlassian.net/=
wiki/spaces/GOCC/pages/16269803539/Rapid+Recovery+Information+Hub" data-lin=
ked-resource-id=3D"16269803539" data-linked-resource-version=3D"5" data-lin=
ked-resource-type=3D"page">Rapid Recovery Information Hub</a></p>
<ul local-id=3D"59e9be79-b77e-442e-83db-35fc9478be4d">
<li local-id=3D"3de6a9d3-4988-4331-aa2c-cc8035247f13">
<p local-id=3D"de37e45930f8">Teams message and email sent to PS Team</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"cd2f261940e8">
<p local-id=3D"b07048b4e935">PS Team to assign members to draft RRP</p></li=
>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"a9413b88-fde6-4900-95e6-5086ccd746a8">
<p local-id=3D"3a49f581c351"><strong>Laptop and JPE/JPW monitoring/Syntheti=
c Job Monitor Agents/minions </strong>- Confirm <a href=3D"https://manulife=
-ets.atlassian.net/wiki/x/foBe0AM" rel=3D"nofollow"><u>new minion set up</u=
></a> and dashboard</p>
<ul local-id=3D"095b98a1-e433-4221-820b-79973f039e02">
<li local-id=3D"5725227f-7f45-4a36-b5af-8bff79b6b7a8">
<p local-id=3D"fedf08945c24"><strong>JPE/JPW still needs VNET update</stron=
g> - Dates TBC - ongoing</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6d9b24a8c8ef">
<li local-id=3D"684fb1986197">
<p local-id=3D"0ac43efed2f6">Non-Prod VNET complete - Post-provisioning iss=
ue waiting for it to be fixed</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5a080eab14bd">
<p local-id=3D"f4907e3d2fe1">Prod VNET setup in progress - Still waiting</p=
></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"eba9729b-60f5-455a-9059-e7c46800ed52">
<p local-id=3D"aa3f8f37a23c"><strong>JP Branch Offices</strong>: 10x laptop=
s in service</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c76c0cf8-44dc-4922-b5cc-9954eb52f18e">
<p local-id=3D"ca5eb12c4fa8"><strong>Philippine Branch Offices</strong>: Vi=
gnesh will work with GOCC on setting up a dashboard</p>
<ul local-id=3D"08a7a35ded6a">
<li local-id=3D"a1ca04612f42">
<p local-id=3D"628876818142">Call between Aleksei, Donna, Vignesh requireme=
nts gathering</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4858d564285c">
<p local-id=3D"742e7bad936b">REQ to install agent in-progress</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e3b0ba7f479a">&nbsp;</p>
<hr local-id=3D"64f15b4e">
<h1 local-id=3D"8e7385b6a4b3" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Decis=
ions">Decisions</h1>
<ul local-id=3D"2cb06587-ee60-477e-b9a7-de9b313a1e14">
<li local-id=3D"e123b5ee-b804-47d5-8607-686d2acf15fe">
<p local-id=3D"ec7feb8e3ae7">Inventory and compliance monitoring of shared =
drive ACLs, focusing on easy cleanup.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0a33a657-5123-4cf8-8421-f3e60e911228">
<p local-id=3D"b35529b9d205">Trim alerting to actionable signals and set up=
 meaningful alerts.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eafa4829-7956-4a63-963c-5b20a969878c">
<p local-id=3D"81ecbe4140f0">Implement daily summary emails for system heal=
th and improve dashboard coverage.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2ed49513-e881-4b41-b73b-243d78715ffd">
<p local-id=3D"881bcad3fd25">Share MMM Level 2 checklist and project plan w=
ith Japan application teams.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e2f6c1fd-e50f-4324-8468-4766cae5f45e">
<p local-id=3D"734f1f390fe3">Include decision matrix in rapid recovery plan=
s for server restart authorization.</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"6c96a399426b" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Openq=
uestions">Open questions</h1>
<ul local-id=3D"891bb097-522a-4b55-b95c-48220abb8fe8">
<li local-id=3D"7138694a-8b4e-4750-98d3-aba8bbabb1c7">
<p local-id=3D"440b22f09b57">Inventory of ACLs is unclear and needs further=
 investigation.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"db9e4a0b-c428-4cb0-8cf6-ff0a419d2716">
<p local-id=3D"aa81e7ddbc52">Ownership of ACL monitoring and cleanup is unr=
esolved.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2bd2bdc0-ea1e-4529-8e9d-ea2532e78d27">
<p local-id=3D"d34432211b05">Refine alerting rules to handle sleeping syste=
ms and avoid false alerts.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9832a155-cf10-401b-9062-2bd98ad70a9b">
<p local-id=3D"04f2e9fa170b">APM activation date for Ingenium production is=
 not determined.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0325a322-11cf-46a8-bf45-d3e7c93f6d9a">
<p local-id=3D"5410d47dd7d1">Responsibility for ADX monitoring and onboardi=
ng in Asia is undecided.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9fa0b1dd-701e-4468-9878-c3130e21e441">
<p local-id=3D"4a818bcc9522">Process for identifying and onboarding applica=
tions to ADX needs clarification.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d30929ba-ef02-4dad-ab8f-a892d1f40f0c">
<p local-id=3D"e3fec4021489">Objectives for file transfer, batch jobs, and =
patching projects are undefined.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"95307bf1-7b48-451e-9506-93dc1d31faa6">
<p local-id=3D"6c878a64b8aa">Authorization for server restarts needs more d=
ocumentation and guardrails.</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"6afa3852c6e1" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Agend=
a">Agenda</h1>
<p local-id=3D"7d5c7251056c"><strong>Goal:</strong> Review ongoing results<=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"9a9669fd-36c3-4278-8c54-e259f46da58c">
<li local-id=3D"dc734cce-1238-4741-82be-f2d20554b7a2">
<p local-id=3D"063db66db4b5">Ongoing results review for Dashboards and tagg=
ing (15 min)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5acfce29-3f9a-456f-a310-d46ae9c35d17">
<p local-id=3D"980bba3be8b4">Ongoing results review for OMM L2 Coverage (15=
 min)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3eb19130-bdea-4c7e-bce5-eaa1c314bd99">
<p local-id=3D"20b69a7c27e6">Ongoing results review for Laptop and JPE/JPW =
monitoring/minions (15 min)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cfd652ae-b0f0-4021-8778-c10c8c44af13">
<p local-id=3D"162464bb948b">Ongoing results review for Rapid Recovery (15 =
min)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"01ad4224-4bfe-4eb9-bf8c-88303787b2d8">
<p local-id=3D"76e0e1373b57">Establish monitoring for folder permissions as=
 part of File transfer/File share (1 min)</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"23e38b0b512a" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Meeti=
ngnotes">Meeting notes</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"9e2fb2062900" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Proje=
ctupdates">Project updates</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"1ed871b7-48f5-49f6-aa6b-24ae89b27da4">
<li local-id=3D"fa7aa9bc-cb61-4d12-9339-d29bcb845635">
<p local-id=3D"6801d8502e65">David explained that the team is actively work=
ing on the developer dashboard with the AQA team, focusing on alerting para=
meters.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7462b316-7bfc-43ae-8f4c-e3017e42724b">
<p local-id=3D"7caa41bb4e70">David described ongoing efforts with MK and Ra=
e to refine developer dashboard alerts, aiming to reduce non-actionable not=
ifications and improve responder routing.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"9d99ba392e52" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Acces=
scontrolandcompliance">Access control and compliance</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"d7d0dd7a-cc88-427d-8b8a-a22c571c929a">
<li local-id=3D"55a9491a-e36e-43cf-9874-16c9b3e24534">
<p local-id=3D"72966dc4d4a2">David described the issue of outdated and inco=
rrectly assigned accounts in shared drive ACLs and mentioned that Aleksei d=
eveloped a compliance checker to identify these patterns.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a734f1a9-8a00-4d06-a659-f5a2ea27f9ff">
<p local-id=3D"3664f6d811e8">Birger explained that the lack of inventory an=
d monitoring for shared drive ACLs has led to accumulation of outdated acco=
unts, and previous systems like Veronis were decommissioned without replace=
ment.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"525dc82d-3282-4420-9518-aee44eab9279">
<p local-id=3D"2653bf41aa4e">Debamalya confirmed that issues with invalid a=
ccounts and unclear ACL ownership persist, and suggested checking with Dong=
 for existing scripts or monitoring solutions.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"000c48a8-051f-4225-8d3f-bace816646f2">
<p local-id=3D"d4c2826da7f8">Kiran explained that migration projects are co=
mplicated by the lack of consolidated information on ACL ownership and outd=
ated accounts, making it difficult to implement effective cleanup strategie=
s and retention policies.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"62c82839-e0cc-4498-8226-fc41575f1aaa">
<p local-id=3D"013f35b19867">Birger described the absence of a regular inve=
ntory and process for identifying folders with only invalid users, leading =
to persistent issues with outdated files and unclear ownership.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4df9e8c5-b4f7-4536-a11d-b371f2a86283">
<p local-id=3D"567401d24602">David highlighted that current folder retentio=
n policies are not enforced due to unclear responsibilities for cleanup, re=
sulting in files from as far back as 1994 remaining undeleted.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"20577f0e-792d-420d-8aeb-04dd7f4de0ea">
<p local-id=3D"9d6a8c5aa76c">David explained that the lack of consolidated =
ownership and ACL information continues to hinder file server migrations an=
d retention policy enforcement.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"26081ee3540d" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Dashb=
oardandalerting">Dashboard and alerting</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"e06dc3cb-e531-498e-ae72-4fe6e90a4117">
<li local-id=3D"75aa1213-ebd0-4fb3-98ee-20b6f038bac4">
<p local-id=3D"7d1d216f9f51">Rae created a daily summary email that provide=
s a concise view of system health, including response times and alert statu=
ses for all Japan systems.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d657dae9-544e-401c-907f-d38000574afb">
<p local-id=3D"df9a2eac047d">Debamalya explained that New Relic supports cu=
stom alert subscriptions, allowing users to receive alerts only for specifi=
c systems or environments they are interested in.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"27e986e9-9388-4508-bcd9-97e568ce4c90">
<p local-id=3D"9946e5ce7692">Debamalya explained that New Relic allows user=
s to subscribe to alerts for specific workloads, enabling tailored notifica=
tions based on system or environment preferences.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4fd82908-02c8-4fc1-a2e7-1909008479b0">
<p local-id=3D"7caf00d84b49">Debamalya described ongoing entity tagging eff=
orts, noting that around 10,001 entities were tagged last week, and that by=
 July or August, users will be able to search and filter entities, alerts, =
and workloads in New Relic using PM IDs.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7e161f45-f3b7-4cf9-b8a0-f4569f4b229f">
<p local-id=3D"619272f2cac2">David clarified that the signal to noise ratio=
 report implementation after the change freeze was not an update from Debam=
alya's team, and Debamalya confirmed no related actions from their side.</p=
></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"b51f784eb29e" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-MMMle=
vel2progress">MMM level 2 progress</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"17dd2605-430f-4183-9106-6437b30b4c3a">
<li local-id=3D"585399d2-6b67-48ae-9878-893b897925de">
<p local-id=3D"a16635683f77">Harish reached out to all Japan application ow=
ners for MMM level 2 updates, and completed data collection for Ingenium; u=
pdates for the remaining applications are expected by Friday.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"947d3dea496c" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-APMro=
llout">APM rollout</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"9fbb1c08-ccaa-4127-aff2-090b8445cd83">
<li local-id=3D"dc79cbe1-fe82-4d1d-a176-7814c5875ad8">
<p local-id=3D"d31a7c3a9d1e">Angelito confirmed that APM was successfully c=
onfigured for non-production environments with Sai, and production rollout =
is planned next.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d5367d64-41b8-4f19-a012-a5ec515b5521">
<p local-id=3D"491ccf21516f">APM was successfully configured for Ingenium's=
 non-production environments, and production rollout is pending scheduling =
due to required outage (Angelito, Sai)</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"1587e8bf7b7f" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Centr=
alizedlogging(ADX)">Centralized logging (ADX)</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"63939de8-5ff3-4956-b416-887ba6c82666">
<li local-id=3D"8ea1fb01-232f-43e9-86a6-c594c6ad98fc">
<p local-id=3D"236f2efb9d3a">David explained that access to ADX centralized=
 logging is available to anyone with proper permissions, and emphasized the=
 need for an Asia-based team to take responsibility for monitoring and mana=
ging ADX logs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"121b75d1-8cea-4054-8168-a8c7289471c4">
<p local-id=3D"deaa690b0a79">Debamalya explained that MoogsoftAlertIntakeDe=
v can be used to validate whether an application's logs are reaching ADX, a=
nd if logs are missing, onboarding instructions should be provided to the a=
pplication teams.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8fed5c1f-51a4-44b0-83e1-ab4d72aea839">
<p local-id=3D"46d2a6545883">Debamalya clarified that ADX log onboarding is=
 the responsibility of application owners, and support is available through=
 the catalog if logs are not reaching ADX</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b233888c-2306-4c65-a18d-f2777e5c0ceb">
<p local-id=3D"56c97d7b75af">Debamalya confirmed that ADX-related tasks wer=
e removed from the R2R scope after discussions with Tabitha and Hari</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"5741386d-d5f6-42d9-a2e4-5c1119fad392">
<p local-id=3D"8d96595c772d">Jonan explained that the ADX log onboarding ta=
sk was dropped from the R2R scope after discussions with Hari and Tabitha.<=
/p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"8937c1263816" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Rapid=
recoveryplan">Rapid recovery plan</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"26f8877f-5d5f-4a4e-a148-34ed2f452889">
<li local-id=3D"1ba13004-b894-4a96-9d85-02ad9ca7de93">
<p local-id=3D"2251164bd9ff">David created a workflow for PS team members t=
o generate rapid recovery plans using AI, but emphasized that the PS team n=
eeds to assign someone to start drafting the plans.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"f2c03f04ad0c" id=3D"id-20260609LapuLapuETS,GOCCandObs-Japan=
